	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10498260659992><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=10498260659992>RE: Should I start over?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=10498260659992#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=206683><span id= >Rarespawn</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>10 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Apr 8th 2:57 PM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Xia, I'll have to agree with Zetol here.&nbsp;&nbsp;It will really depend on your style of play.  But, I wanted to offer some reassurance from another High Elf wiz, and encourage you to stick with it a little longer.  Wizards really start to come into their own after you hit 30 or so.  At about your level, you really are going to stop meleeing almost entirely.  Don't worry about your combat skills so much, you aren't going to rely on them so much as you advance.  Circle of Force at 34 is coming up for you (quadding, yay!), you get a decent nuke with Inferno Shock at 29.  With KEI you should have plenty of mana if you're wanting to solo, which I'm guessing you are, since I wouldn't think you'd need to finish off a mob with meleeing in a group, except maybe to practice your skills.  And the INT difference between high elves and erudites is something you can overcome with some equipment upgrades.  I don't know what you're equiped with, but there are lots of INT upgrade items available in the bazaar for reasonable prices.  At your level, I'd say just try to get your INT up to 200.  Save your coin and get Golden Efreeti Boots, a decent robe (Froggy, Shiny Metallic), that's like 17 INT right there.  Carry around an INT food (Blackened Teir'Dal, Misty Thicket Picnic)in your first slot and force eat other food.  All I'm saying is every little bit helps.<br>By the mid game, you're up there in INT right there with the other races of wizards.  It ends up depending on your gear so much, the 15 points less you start with is almost moot.<br>Good luck to you.  I hope you stick with it a little longer to see just how good wizards get.<br><br><br>Hycliff<br>49 wiz<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
