	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The hunting guide at www.graffe.com is pretty handy, and a KEI will help in large amounts.&nbsp;&nbsp;That said, though, you have tons of options for where to hunt.  If you want to solo, it never hurts to have a SoW.  I would hit up your nearest newbie zones for first several levels.  Each one is pretty safe.  When you get bored there, though, North Ro and Oasis offer decent experience.  Oasis is still great because you can take on crocs and not get aggro from other crocs.  And Lake of Ill Omen is a decent place to group after 18 or so, and the Overthere is good for your low 30's.  Once you hit 34 don't be afraid to try your hand at some quadding, and also, properly played, you can solo some Hill Giants in N Karana.  Yep, they con red, and yep, you better have a sow and KEI, but a snare that holds and every nuke you got will take one of those guys down, and through about 37 or so, is a pretty good experience source.  While you're waiting for another to pop, you can always harrass the occasional lt blue and blue griffenne and griffon, and turn in greater lightstones for the research book to the bandit there in N Karana which you can sell back for some plat.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
