	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f104802342388973><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=104802342388973>RE: Quading</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=104802342388973#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=206683><span id= >Rarespawn</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>10 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Mar 18th 5:11 PM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hey Zetol.&nbsp;&nbsp;I wanted to throw in my 2cp's worth here as well.  I really agree with Brodicius on his recommendation that you go to Eastern Wastes.  There are generally lots of walruses and ulthorks around (plus you can hang on to those ulthork tusks for pretty good plat items from the Othimir quest), and it is pretty safe.  I think the congestion of mobs in OT makes it a little less safe for quadding, because there aren't so many clear lanes to kite your mobs without much risk of adds.  In EW, I can't remember the last time I got an add that I wasn't trying to get.  You get a pretty good feel for some of the safe lanes in EW fairly quickly I think.  I recommend pulling the walruses and ulthorks toward the north beach cliff and then moving east or west depending on what's clear.  Also, I recommend that you use O'Kiel's Levity, because if there are more mobs that you don't want to add, you can steer off the cliff a little ways as you're heading east or west and not fall and avoid the add.  Plus, if you're needing to put some distance between you and the mobs more quickly, I have noticed that if you go over the edges of the cliffs that kind of jut in and out heading west, they have to go down and come back up and lose more distance as you basically cruise straight across.  It saves time on your bonds of force as well.  Hope that helps some.<br><br><br>Hycliff<br>44 wiz<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
