	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Mar 24th 5:33 PM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Gravity Flux is an aoE spell, and not a good one to use when quadding. TFlux is the Staff of Temporate Flux which does the little debuff. You do not have to have the TFlux Staff equipped in Pri/Sec ... just keep it in your inventory and hot-key it for a right-click. The reason it works so well to pull for quadding is that the R-Click effect, the debuff, has a zero cast time (thus you cast on the run) and pretty close to a zero recast time.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
