	   <tr><td colspan=2>Okay Aysdf I know people that do the /pet get lost thing too, and it works.&nbsp;&nbsp;Don't know why they made it like that though.  I know from experience that the pet gets lost on its own, but you will not lose the effects even if it is not around.  Your pet can get hit with AE spells, and that same  buff, firetree's,  that you are talking about will also help it with more hitpoints, I have actually had my familiar die from AE zone and the pet reappear.  I have a feeling that this is just a bug and no one reported it, I couldn't see them doing this intentionally.  The flapping wings are annoying at times though, but at least we don't have to recast it everytime we zone.  I hope in all this rambling I actually helped you out with your question, happy hunting.<br>&nbsp;<br>Brodicius <br>53 Wizard<br>unguilded<br>Tunare</td></tr>
